    "body": "## Problem\r\nin #38001 Justinmk suggested improving the security of the allow action by \r\n - 1 showing a passive warning.\r\n - 2 hash the buffer contents rather than on-disk contents if the file is loaded.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\n- 1 I modified the `compute_hash` function in `runtime/lua/vim/secure.lua` to make the function hash the buffer of the file if it's loaded in memory or fallback to hashing the contents of the file on disk.\r\n\r\n- 2 i refactored the code a little bit by adding a new `get_buf_content` function to not repeat the code of getting the buffer content.\r\n\r\n- 3 added a passive warning to the user when trusting a file using path.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-19T02:21:42Z",
